WEBVTT

00:04.265 --> 00:04.482
.

00:04.526 --> 00:07.355
[ominous music]

00:07.398 --> 00:11.272
- We can fix the machine
and save your wife.

00:11.315 --> 00:13.535
We're so close to a solution.

00:13.578 --> 00:15.537
- It's all James has and
it's part of a larger equation.

00:15.580 --> 00:18.018
But if we can find the rest,
we'll get the answer.

00:19.845 --> 00:21.412
- Sam says
it's a pretty bad concussion.

00:21.456 --> 00:23.327
- Mom!
- Let's get her on the bus.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.068
- I have a brain tumor
and you have a treatment.

00:25.112 --> 00:26.504
- A cure.

00:26.548 --> 00:28.028
During your intake,
you told my guards

00:28.071 --> 00:29.333
you're a psychiatrist.

00:29.377 --> 00:31.988
Do you think we could
arrange a time to chat?

00:32.031 --> 00:33.337
- Those flowers.

00:33.381 --> 00:35.731
- They're the ones
Aaron used to make you draw.

00:35.774 --> 00:37.428
- Maybe he knew about
this place.

00:37.472 --> 00:38.951
[snarling]
- No!

00:38.995 --> 00:41.128
- Maybe there's a bigger
reason why we're here.

00:41.171 --> 00:42.477
- Even when he's not here,

00:42.520 --> 00:45.480
he finds his way
back into my head.

00:45.523 --> 00:47.699
- I think Taamet's the killer.

00:47.743 --> 00:50.267
I went to his cell and I saw
the same symbol up close.

00:50.311 --> 00:51.616
- Why would you go to his cell?

00:51.660 --> 00:53.357
- 'Cause I'm the one that
let Taamet go.

00:53.401 --> 00:55.533
You accused Virgil
with no proof.

00:55.577 --> 00:58.188
- Virgil spent time
with the Exiles.

00:58.232 --> 01:01.452
I'm telling you, he's our guy.

01:05.717 --> 01:08.633
[serene music]

01:08.676 --> 01:10.853
♪

01:10.896 --> 01:14.770
[rhino grunting and chewing]

01:18.252 --> 01:20.732
[otherworldly thrumming]

01:20.776 --> 01:23.692
[rhino snorts]

01:27.348 --> 01:31.091
[rhino bellows]

01:31.134 --> 01:34.050
[suspenseful music]

01:34.094 --> 01:40.883
♪

01:47.194 --> 01:49.109
- Morning.

01:49.892 --> 01:51.198
- Morning.

01:51.241 --> 01:53.765
- We brought you breakfast.

01:53.809 --> 01:54.896
How you feeling?

01:54.940 --> 01:56.985
- The concussion's still there.

01:57.029 --> 01:58.770
My leg is better though.

01:58.814 --> 02:01.382
I don't think I'll be leaving
the bus anytime today.

02:01.425 --> 02:04.254
At least your dad
left me some flowers.

02:04.298 --> 02:06.213
- Where'd he go?

02:06.256 --> 02:08.650
- To see James.

02:08.693 --> 02:10.695
- I can't believe Dad thinks
he can trust him.

02:10.739 --> 02:12.349
- He's just trying to
keep Mom alive.

02:12.393 --> 02:15.700
- Hey, guys, I know it's
dangerous down here.

02:15.744 --> 02:17.876
But we have to face things
as they come.

02:17.920 --> 02:19.791
And I just--

02:19.835 --> 02:21.966
I wish your dad knew that James
wasn't the way to do that.

02:22.011 --> 02:23.534
- Yes, exactly.

02:23.578 --> 02:25.406
- If there's even a chance
that James can help Mom,

02:25.449 --> 02:26.972
we need to look into it.

02:27.016 --> 02:29.192
We have to do something.

02:29.236 --> 02:30.933
Right?

02:30.976 --> 02:34.805
- Yes, but for now, um...

02:34.850 --> 02:37.635
why don't you give me
some water?

02:41.291 --> 02:42.597
[sighs]

02:51.519 --> 02:54.652
[soft tense music]

02:54.696 --> 02:58.090
♪

02:58.134 --> 02:59.309
- Hey.

02:59.353 --> 03:01.355
What are you up to?

03:01.398 --> 03:03.487
- Uh, I was actually, uh,

03:03.531 --> 03:05.185
coming to give you
one of these.

03:05.228 --> 03:08.971
But, uh, got distracted
by Virgil.

03:09.014 --> 03:13.584
I know everyone thinks
Taamet killed Wyatt but

03:13.628 --> 03:16.500
my gut's telling me Virgil
had something to do with it.

03:16.544 --> 03:19.851
- I trust your gut.

03:19.895 --> 03:23.246
- Thanks.

03:23.290 --> 03:27.337
You know, you always make me
feel better about the world.

03:30.297 --> 03:32.690
I've been--I've been
thinking about something.

03:32.734 --> 03:35.780
Um, you know how
you been talking about

03:35.824 --> 03:40.829
making a fresh start?
- Mm-hmm.

03:40.872 --> 03:44.485
- Well, I was wondering,

03:44.528 --> 03:47.923
maybe you'd, I don't know,
wanna move in with me?

03:47.966 --> 03:50.969
[chuckles]

03:51.013 --> 03:54.364
- That's sweet.

03:56.061 --> 03:58.847
But I just don't think
now's a good time.

03:58.890 --> 04:00.065
- OK, cool.

04:00.109 --> 04:02.720
Yeah, no, it was just--
just a thought.

04:02.764 --> 04:05.070
- I'll talk to you later, OK?

04:05.114 --> 04:12.252
♪

04:16.343 --> 04:18.257
- Hey.

04:19.084 --> 04:20.695
- Virgil.

04:20.738 --> 04:22.305
What are you doing up here?

04:22.349 --> 04:23.915
- Here to relieve you.

04:23.959 --> 04:26.353
- Uh, Judah's supposed to
relieve me,

04:26.396 --> 04:28.093
and not for another two hours.

04:28.137 --> 04:29.747
- Right.

04:29.791 --> 04:31.053
Thought you could use a break.

04:31.096 --> 04:32.750
- I promised Sam that
I'd watch the clearing

04:32.794 --> 04:34.622
while the search party's gone.

04:34.665 --> 04:37.451
Taamet could come back
and we need to be ready.

04:37.494 --> 04:39.322
- Yeah, I get that.

04:39.366 --> 04:41.193
It's just ever since
Lucas locked me up,

04:41.237 --> 04:43.370
I've been getting these
weird looks from everybody,

04:43.413 --> 04:44.936
like they don't trust me
or something.

04:44.980 --> 04:46.329
I was hoping I could
come up here

04:46.373 --> 04:49.767
and just show them
I'm on their side.

04:49.811 --> 04:51.987
Come on, man.
At least let me cover for you

04:52.030 --> 04:55.991
so you can get some breakfast,
yeah?

05:01.779 --> 05:05.000
- All right. Fine.
I'll be right back.

05:05.043 --> 05:07.959
[ominous music]

05:08.003 --> 05:14.923
♪

05:38.468 --> 05:39.730
- [whistles]

05:43.908 --> 05:45.867
- Tell the others.

05:45.909 --> 05:48.217
It's time.

05:48.260 --> 05:50.350
[bird screeches]

05:50.393 --> 05:53.483
[wind rushing softly]

05:53.527 --> 05:55.485
[rustling]

05:55.529 --> 05:58.445
[suspenseful music]

05:58.488 --> 06:05.626
♪

06:09.281 --> 06:11.936
- Hold it. Don't move.

06:11.980 --> 06:13.460
♪

06:13.503 --> 06:15.940
Turn around slow, really slow.

06:15.984 --> 06:20.205
♪

06:20.249 --> 06:22.686
Levi?

06:22.730 --> 06:24.645
- It's great seeing you, too.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.563
[dramatic music]

06:29.606 --> 06:31.391
♪

06:34.481 --> 06:34.916
.

06:34.959 --> 06:37.875
- Hey! Hey.
[chuckles softly]

06:37.919 --> 06:39.050
- How's Eve and the kids?

06:39.094 --> 06:40.878
- Yeah, they're safe.

06:40.922 --> 06:42.489
What are you doing here?

06:42.532 --> 06:44.665
What happened to your hair?

06:44.707 --> 06:46.493
It's barely been a week.
Wha--

06:46.536 --> 06:47.929
- Down here it's been a week.

06:47.972 --> 06:50.584
It's been ten years for me
since I saw you in '88.

06:50.627 --> 06:51.628
- What do you mean?

06:51.672 --> 06:53.804
- I went down a sinkhole
in 1998.

06:55.415 --> 06:57.678
- [clears throat]

06:57.721 --> 06:58.940
'98?

06:58.983 --> 07:01.464
- New sinkholes,
they just keep opening up.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.727
So I assume your mission to
destroy the machine failed.

07:03.771 --> 07:05.990
- Yeah, well,

07:06.034 --> 07:08.079
we damaged it, but, um,

07:08.123 --> 07:09.777
the portal's still open.

07:09.820 --> 07:11.082
- You know, after we split,

07:11.126 --> 07:13.824
I never stopped trying to
bring you guys home.

07:13.868 --> 07:15.260
I joined with the DOD.

07:15.304 --> 07:16.957
They got a team trying to
stop the sinkholes

07:17.001 --> 07:19.003
and rescue everyone trapped
down here.

07:19.047 --> 07:21.702
- So you're gonna
bring us all back?

07:21.745 --> 07:22.659
- That's the plan.

07:22.703 --> 07:24.835
- [chuckles]

07:24.879 --> 07:26.097
I don't know what to say.

07:26.141 --> 07:27.316
- Well, thank you is
a good start.

07:27.359 --> 07:28.448
- OK. Thank you.

07:28.491 --> 07:30.493
- [chuckles]

07:30.537 --> 07:32.277
- You know, the truth is,

07:32.321 --> 07:35.455
I'm working on the same thing
with James.

07:35.498 --> 07:36.804
- James?

07:36.847 --> 07:38.240
Like, your father, James?
- I know.

07:38.283 --> 07:39.589
Last you heard of him,
he was dangerous,

07:39.633 --> 07:40.895
but it's complicated.

07:40.938 --> 07:42.940
He's working on a way
to fix the machine.

07:42.984 --> 07:44.289
I'm on my way to talk to him
right now.

07:44.332 --> 07:47.249
In fact, why--
why don't you see for yourself?

07:48.642 --> 07:50.731
- OK.

07:50.774 --> 07:52.254
Let's go see James.

07:52.297 --> 07:53.560
- Yeah.

07:56.171 --> 07:58.826
You know, it's brave,
what you did.

07:58.869 --> 08:00.958
It's dangerous.
No certain way back.

08:01.002 --> 08:02.786
- You did the same thing.

08:02.830 --> 08:05.049
- It's different.

08:05.093 --> 08:07.487
I did it for my family.

08:07.530 --> 08:09.401
- You guys are my family.

08:14.842 --> 08:17.801
[soft tense music]

08:17.845 --> 08:20.848
♪

08:20.891 --> 08:23.024
- Thank you.

08:25.592 --> 08:27.507
- These are for you.

08:30.031 --> 08:31.946
- Dr. Coleman,
how are you feeling?

08:31.989 --> 08:33.207
- I know I've only had
one round of this,

08:33.251 --> 08:35.818
but I feel better already.

08:35.863 --> 08:37.778
- Excellent.

08:37.821 --> 08:39.431
This is a tablet for
taking notes

08:39.475 --> 08:41.563
during your therapy session
with James.

08:41.607 --> 08:43.174
Though, if you don't mind,

08:43.217 --> 08:45.742
I am curious about
a few things.

08:45.786 --> 08:47.091
- Such as?

08:47.135 --> 08:48.179
- Would you say there is

08:48.223 --> 08:49.746
an ethical conflict,

08:49.790 --> 08:52.880
considering your relationship
with his extended family?

08:52.923 --> 08:56.057
- Well, as a professional,

08:56.100 --> 08:59.451
I always put my patient's
interests first.

08:59.495 --> 09:00.322
So, no.

09:00.365 --> 09:02.716
No ethical conflict present.

09:02.759 --> 09:04.152
- Even though you
stand to benefit

09:04.195 --> 09:05.849
from his work to
fix the machine

09:05.893 --> 09:07.677
and potentially send you home?

09:07.721 --> 09:09.070
- No.

09:09.113 --> 09:11.202
I'm getting married to
a member of the fort.

09:11.246 --> 09:13.640
So my plan isn't to return,
but to stay here.

09:13.683 --> 09:17.034
I'd also like to request
a legal pad, if that's OK?

09:17.078 --> 09:18.035
For privacy.

09:18.079 --> 09:20.124
- Of course.

09:20.168 --> 09:22.605
Staying offline is smart.

09:22.649 --> 09:25.434
Around here,
there are eyes everywhere.

09:30.613 --> 09:31.962
[drawer shuts]

09:35.705 --> 09:37.489
Have a good session.

09:39.535 --> 09:42.494
[ominous music]

09:42.538 --> 09:46.760
♪

09:46.803 --> 09:49.023
- Someone came this way.

09:49.066 --> 09:51.112
Could be Taamet.

09:51.155 --> 09:55.682
Let's do a quick sweep.
Everyone spread out.

09:55.725 --> 09:57.205
I'm glad you're out here
with me.

09:57.248 --> 09:59.903
We need to do everything we can
to protect ourselves.

09:59.947 --> 10:01.209
Particularly,
since it looks like

10:01.252 --> 10:03.124
we're not getting out of here
any time soon.

10:06.431 --> 10:07.781
- If I tell you something,

10:07.824 --> 10:09.434
will you promise not to tell
anyone else about it?

10:09.478 --> 10:10.827
- Well, I do know a thing or
two about

10:10.871 --> 10:13.177
how to keep things classified.

10:13.221 --> 10:16.441
Yes, I promise.
- OK.

10:16.485 --> 10:19.401
Yesterday, Caroline and I found
some of Dr. Moore's research.

10:19.444 --> 10:20.750
She said she had to
look into it first,

10:20.794 --> 10:23.100
but it could mean that
fixing James's machine is

10:23.144 --> 10:25.842
a real possibility.
- What?

10:25.886 --> 10:28.671
- But she made me promise
not to tell anyone about it,

10:28.715 --> 10:30.020
including Josh.

10:30.064 --> 10:32.588
Dad, I had to lie to him.

10:35.330 --> 10:36.723
- You did what you had to do.

10:36.766 --> 10:38.638
Look, back when
I was doing missions,

10:38.681 --> 10:40.465
there were plenty of times
your mom wanted to know

10:40.509 --> 10:43.643
what I was up to,
but I couldn't tell her.

10:43.686 --> 10:46.515
- Did she understand?

10:46.558 --> 10:49.213
- She did.

10:49.257 --> 10:51.607
- There's smoke
coming from that way.

10:51.651 --> 10:52.956
[dark music]

10:53.000 --> 10:54.566
- Could be Taamet.

10:54.610 --> 10:56.612
Everyone stay close.

10:56.656 --> 11:03.575
♪

11:06.056 --> 11:10.104
- It's an Exile symbol.

11:10.147 --> 11:11.671
- So where did they go?

11:11.714 --> 11:16.806
♪

11:16.850 --> 11:19.330
- What the hell was that for?
- For being an idiot.

11:19.374 --> 11:21.681
You need to stop backing Dad
on this James stuff.

11:21.724 --> 11:23.726
Maybe if you, me, and Mom were
on the same page,

11:23.770 --> 11:25.380
he'd see he was being
an idiot too.

11:25.423 --> 11:27.338
- He's not being an idiot, Iz.
We're onto something here.

11:27.382 --> 11:30.602
And if it can help
with Mom's situation,

11:30.646 --> 11:31.865
we'd be idiots not to
look into it.

11:31.908 --> 11:33.127
- All you found was a key that

11:33.170 --> 11:34.432
nobody has any idea
what it's for.

11:34.476 --> 11:35.825
- Then how do you explain
Caroline?

11:35.869 --> 11:38.262
- What about her?
- She disappeared this morning.

11:38.306 --> 11:39.742
Didn't tell anyone
where she's going.

11:39.786 --> 11:42.397
There is something more
going on here,

11:42.440 --> 11:47.794
and we're gonna find out what,
whether you help us or not.

11:47.837 --> 11:50.535
[suspenseful music]

11:50.579 --> 11:53.756
[shouting]

11:53.800 --> 11:55.279
- Josh. Josh, run.

11:55.323 --> 11:56.324
Go, go, go!
- Come on!

11:56.367 --> 11:58.152
- [shouting]
- Hurry!

11:58.195 --> 12:00.676
- [shouting]

12:04.941 --> 12:06.813
- Ow! [grunts]

12:06.856 --> 12:08.771
- Holy Mother of God.

12:08.815 --> 12:10.991
- What?
- Oh, my God!

12:11.034 --> 12:12.993
- [grunts]

12:13.036 --> 12:15.778
- Get in the car.

12:15.822 --> 12:18.476
- [panting]

12:18.520 --> 12:19.782
- [grunts]
- Ah!

12:19.826 --> 12:21.262
- Get off!

12:21.305 --> 12:23.264
- Lock them all up.
- [straining]

12:23.307 --> 12:25.396
- [grunts]
Get off me!

12:27.616 --> 12:30.837
[grunting]

12:30.880 --> 12:34.144
[indistinct shouting]

12:34.188 --> 12:35.929
- What are they doing?
- [shouting]

12:35.972 --> 12:38.975
[people screaming]

12:39.019 --> 12:43.110
[indistinct shouting]

12:44.502 --> 12:46.983
- Hey! Hey, why didn't you
warn us? Huh?

12:47.027 --> 12:48.419
You were on the tower.
You could see them coming.

12:48.463 --> 12:50.552
Why didn't you say anything?
- [grunts]

12:50.595 --> 12:52.249
Get the hell away from me!

12:52.293 --> 12:53.773
- Get in there!
- [grunts]

12:53.816 --> 12:56.253
- What's going on out there?
[indistinct screaming]

12:56.297 --> 12:59.169
[dark dramatic music]

12:59.213 --> 13:02.216
♪

13:02.259 --> 13:04.958
- The Exiles are back.

13:05.001 --> 13:06.742
♪

13:11.094 --> 13:11.268
.

13:11.312 --> 13:14.228
- What did you do?
- Nothing!

13:14.271 --> 13:15.925
[grunts]

13:15.969 --> 13:18.058
- You have the same look on
your face you had yesterday.

13:18.101 --> 13:20.016
And I knew you were
lying then, too!

13:20.060 --> 13:23.106
- You're wrong, man.
- Am I? Huh? Am I?

13:23.150 --> 13:24.847
Then tell me why the bandanna
that was on your hand

13:24.891 --> 13:27.545
is now hanging off the tower!

13:27.589 --> 13:30.113
You signaled them.
- I did not!

13:30.157 --> 13:32.986
- These are the same maniacs
you escaped from.

13:33.029 --> 13:37.251
Why did you let them in here?

13:37.294 --> 13:38.643
Huh?

13:38.687 --> 13:41.168
- I didn't have a choice!

13:41.211 --> 13:44.127
[breathing heavily]

13:47.478 --> 13:50.177
He made me.

13:50.220 --> 13:52.222
- What the hell do they have
on you?

13:52.266 --> 13:56.226
- [breathing heavily]

13:56.270 --> 13:59.186
[soft tense music]

13:59.229 --> 14:06.149
♪

14:13.330 --> 14:15.158
- Dad.

14:15.202 --> 14:16.943
- No, no. Please.

14:16.986 --> 14:19.336
Please, please, please! No!

14:19.380 --> 14:21.121
[breathing rapidly]
No, no, no, no!

14:21.164 --> 14:22.905
- It's OK, it's OK.
We're just here to help.

14:22.949 --> 14:25.386
- I'm gonna cut you loose, OK?

14:25.429 --> 14:27.823
- [panting]

14:27.867 --> 14:30.565
- The Exiles are gone.
You're safe.

14:30.608 --> 14:32.828
I'm Sam.
This is my daughter, Riley.

14:32.872 --> 14:34.395
Can you tell us who you are?

14:34.438 --> 14:35.787
- [panting]

14:35.831 --> 14:37.441
Jane.

14:37.485 --> 14:40.488
- The people that were here,
do you know where they went?

14:40.531 --> 14:41.881
- No.

14:41.924 --> 14:43.447
- Do you remember
how you got here?

14:43.491 --> 14:47.495
- I fell down a sinkhole in
Los Angeles with my husband.

14:47.538 --> 14:50.846
We got captured by these people
who made us work in a mine.

14:50.890 --> 14:52.979
- Is your husband here, too?
- No.

14:53.022 --> 14:57.592
They said they'd kill me
unless Virgil helped them.

14:57.635 --> 15:02.466
- Your husband's name is
Virgil?

15:02.510 --> 15:04.381
If Virgil's been working with
the Exiles

15:04.425 --> 15:07.210
and they're not here...

15:07.254 --> 15:10.387
Get the others. We need to get
back to the clearing now.

15:10.431 --> 15:12.912
[suspenseful music]

15:13.564 --> 15:15.523
- Where is it?

15:15.566 --> 15:16.872
- Tear it apart.

15:16.916 --> 15:18.482
- [screaming]
- Stay there.

15:18.526 --> 15:20.397
- What are they looking for?

15:20.441 --> 15:22.095
- I don't know.

15:22.138 --> 15:24.445
But we gotta get to Mom.
- They will kill you.

15:24.488 --> 15:25.707
- She's got no way to
defend herself.

15:25.750 --> 15:27.796
- Hey, wait, wait.

15:29.624 --> 15:31.234
- Everybody split up!

15:32.757 --> 15:35.543
- I have an idea.

15:35.586 --> 15:37.806
[grunts]

15:37.849 --> 15:39.155
We're gonna use this to
save Mom.

15:39.199 --> 15:41.897
- You, stay in there.

15:41.941 --> 15:44.204
- Did you see
where Josh and Izzy went?

15:44.247 --> 15:46.467
- No.
- Check here.

15:46.510 --> 15:48.338
- Um, OK, stay here.

15:48.382 --> 15:49.774
- Wait, hang on. Hang on!

15:49.818 --> 15:51.646
Whatever we do next,
we have to think this through.

15:51.689 --> 15:54.083
- No. No, no. This is my fault.
I need to fix this.

15:54.127 --> 15:56.607
- What do you mean?
What are you talking about?

15:56.651 --> 15:58.435
- Look, it's not worth getting
into in your condition.

15:58.479 --> 16:01.090
- I disagree. Acting without
thinking things through is

16:01.134 --> 16:02.570
exactly how I got in
this condition.

16:02.613 --> 16:03.875
We need a plan.

16:03.919 --> 16:05.703
- I just don't want
any more bad to come from

16:05.747 --> 16:07.009
what I did.
- Keep searching!

16:07.053 --> 16:08.793
Still haven't found it.

16:08.837 --> 16:11.753
- Hey.

16:11.796 --> 16:13.407
- What are they doing?

16:16.105 --> 16:17.237
We have to get to the kids.

16:17.280 --> 16:18.847
- Eve, whoa!

16:18.890 --> 16:20.675
- Josh. Izzy?

16:20.718 --> 16:22.329
- Eve?

16:22.372 --> 16:24.157
Eve! No.

16:24.200 --> 16:25.419
- We're not leaving
until we find it.

16:25.462 --> 16:28.596
- OK, you're still breathing.
That's good.

16:28.639 --> 16:31.599
[tense music]

16:31.642 --> 16:38.562
♪

16:41.522 --> 16:44.046
Hey! Uh, excuse me? Hello?

16:44.090 --> 16:45.613
Hi. G'day, fellas.

16:45.656 --> 16:48.746
Little awkward but I need to
get meds from my car.

16:48.790 --> 16:50.096
- Go.
- Back where you were!

16:50.139 --> 16:51.706
- Look, look, look,
I don't know if you've ever

16:51.749 --> 16:54.839
seen someone have a full-blown
anxiety attack before,

16:54.883 --> 16:57.190
but, uh, it is not pretty, OK?

16:57.233 --> 17:01.542
We're talking flailing limbs,
verbal outbursts, hives.

17:01.585 --> 17:03.022
Google it.

17:05.154 --> 17:08.417
Uh, but hey, if that's
what you really want,

17:08.462 --> 17:10.768
I can go back to the bus.

17:10.811 --> 17:13.728
♪

17:13.771 --> 17:14.858
- Thought I'd see you.

17:14.903 --> 17:17.210
- Honestly, I was hoping
the opposite.

17:17.252 --> 17:19.907
- What are you doing out here?

17:19.951 --> 17:21.648
Not a good idea.

17:21.692 --> 17:23.085
♪

17:23.128 --> 17:26.045
[both grunting]

17:28.221 --> 17:30.658
- [grunts]
- Oh!

17:30.701 --> 17:32.486
- Take him.

17:32.529 --> 17:37.143
♪

17:43.801 --> 17:44.019
.

17:44.063 --> 17:46.326
- Listen, I've been thinking,
and what you told me

17:46.369 --> 17:47.718
doesn't add up.
- What doesn't?

17:47.762 --> 17:49.981
- Why you came down here.
- What?

17:50.025 --> 17:51.940
- Be straight with me.

17:51.983 --> 17:53.550
There's something
you're not telling me.

17:53.594 --> 17:55.422
- What, you're not happy
to see me?

17:55.465 --> 17:57.076
- That's not it.

17:57.119 --> 18:00.122
Come on.

18:00.166 --> 18:02.646
- You're right.

18:02.690 --> 18:04.170
But it's not what
you're thinking.

18:04.213 --> 18:05.867
- What am I thinking?

18:05.910 --> 18:07.912
- That I'm back for Eve.

18:07.956 --> 18:10.176
- [sighs]

18:10.219 --> 18:13.222
- Gavin, for me,
it's been over a decade.

18:13.266 --> 18:18.488
What happened between her and I
is ancient history.

18:18.532 --> 18:20.186
It's not why I'm back.

18:20.229 --> 18:23.885
- OK.

18:23.928 --> 18:26.801
So why are you back?

18:26.844 --> 18:29.673
- One of the people on my team,

18:29.717 --> 18:33.373
she was more than
just a colleague.

18:33.416 --> 18:36.419
Her name was Marissa.

18:36.463 --> 18:40.206
We fell in love, got married,

18:40.249 --> 18:43.905
and I found peace.

18:43.948 --> 18:46.125
- So what happened?

18:46.168 --> 18:47.778
- She died.

18:51.217 --> 18:52.566
- I'm sorry.

18:52.609 --> 18:54.481
- For a while, I--

18:54.524 --> 18:57.832
I didn't know what to do.

18:57.875 --> 19:01.009
Then I realized,
I could honor her memory

19:01.052 --> 19:05.535
by coming down here and
finishing what she started.

19:05.579 --> 19:09.539
Gavin, that's why I'm here.

19:09.583 --> 19:11.237
- I'm sorry, buddy.

19:11.280 --> 19:13.804
- Thank you.

19:13.848 --> 19:16.285
Someone's coming.

19:16.329 --> 19:19.288
[tense music]

19:19.332 --> 19:23.336
♪

19:23.379 --> 19:25.816
- Sam.

19:25.860 --> 19:26.730
- Levi.

19:26.774 --> 19:28.210
- Man, it is good to see you.

19:28.254 --> 19:29.994
- What the hell's
going on here?

19:30.038 --> 19:31.692
- Levi has got
a lot to tell you.

19:31.735 --> 19:32.954
- I want to hear everything
you two have to say.

19:32.997 --> 19:34.999
But right now,
we have other problems.

19:35.043 --> 19:37.176
We just found out that Virgil's
been working for Taamet.

19:37.219 --> 19:40.091
The Exiles are on the way to
the clearing.

19:40.135 --> 19:43.791
- We need to get there now.

19:46.663 --> 19:49.840
[ominous music]

19:49.884 --> 19:53.409
♪

19:53.453 --> 19:57.457
- Tell me, Doctor,
how are you holding up?

19:57.500 --> 19:59.676
- So far, so good.

19:59.720 --> 20:02.375
But this meeting
isn't about me.

20:02.418 --> 20:05.073
Please.
- Well, thank you for

20:05.116 --> 20:06.553
taking me on as a patient.

20:06.596 --> 20:09.251
I understand my reputation
precedes me.

20:09.295 --> 20:12.689
Likely, you've been talking to
my son, or perhaps his wife.

20:12.733 --> 20:14.691
I know she's not
my biggest fan.

20:14.735 --> 20:16.389
- I like to reserve judgment
for myself.

20:16.432 --> 20:17.433
- Good.

20:17.477 --> 20:20.044
So shall we get started?

20:20.088 --> 20:22.960
- All right.

20:23.004 --> 20:25.093
What would you like to
talk about?

20:25.136 --> 20:27.704
- Uh, well, I haven't slept
in a month,

20:27.748 --> 20:31.621
and I'm starting to worry
it will impact my work.

20:31.665 --> 20:34.058
- Insomnia can have
a variety of causes.

20:34.102 --> 20:36.235
Three of the most common
are medication,

20:36.278 --> 20:38.019
illness, or stress.

20:38.062 --> 20:40.456
- I haven't been sick
in over a year.

20:40.500 --> 20:43.242
I'm not on any medications that
would cause sleeplessness.

20:43.285 --> 20:45.287
- Which leaves stress.

20:45.331 --> 20:48.029
Given your position and
what you do in this building,

20:48.072 --> 20:50.510
I imagine you encounter
quite a lot of it.

20:50.553 --> 20:54.253
So what changed a month ago?

20:54.296 --> 20:57.038
- Nothing.

20:57.081 --> 20:58.866
- Can you describe
what happened during the day

20:58.909 --> 21:01.216
before that
first sleepless night?

21:01.260 --> 21:04.306
- I had some meetings,
read some reports.

21:04.350 --> 21:05.873
- What about that night?

21:05.916 --> 21:09.877
- Well, I remember something
woke me

21:09.920 --> 21:11.182
in the middle of the night,
but I--

21:11.226 --> 21:13.097
I went straight back to sleep.

21:13.141 --> 21:16.623
- Something?

21:16.666 --> 21:19.408
- It was--it was a dream.

21:19.452 --> 21:21.149
- What kind of dream?

21:21.192 --> 21:22.629
- About work.

21:22.672 --> 21:24.761
Uh, we had
a shipment of evergreens

21:24.805 --> 21:27.329
scheduled to be sent.
And in the dream,

21:27.373 --> 21:29.592
I went down to the Bio Bay

21:29.636 --> 21:32.856
and all the trees had lost
their needles.

21:32.900 --> 21:34.336
And I know it
sounds ridiculous,

21:34.380 --> 21:35.598
but they've taken years
to grow.

21:35.642 --> 21:38.122
And I just--
I woke up in a cold sweat.

21:38.166 --> 21:40.995
- It sounds like
a typical anxiety dream.

21:41.038 --> 21:42.997
Stressful,

21:43.040 --> 21:45.521
but nothing that would trigger
a month of insomnia.

21:45.565 --> 21:48.742
You're sure there
wasn't more to it?

21:50.657 --> 21:53.355
- [grunts]

21:53.399 --> 21:55.401
My apologies, Doctor.

21:55.444 --> 21:56.750
I have a meeting
I have to get to.

21:56.793 --> 21:57.925
- But we just got started.

21:57.968 --> 21:59.927
- Ah, I'm sorry.

21:59.970 --> 22:04.323
We will continue
this session soon.

22:04.366 --> 22:06.237
Thank you for your time.

22:12.113 --> 22:13.810
- I get the Exiles forcing you
to spy on us.

22:13.854 --> 22:16.335
But why why'd you kill Wyatt?

22:16.378 --> 22:19.468
- I didn't want to.

22:19.512 --> 22:21.818
Look, a few days ago,

22:21.862 --> 22:23.516
Taamet told me to search
Caroline's bag,

22:23.559 --> 22:25.344
and, uh--and I did.

22:25.387 --> 22:27.911
And Wyatt, he saw me.

22:27.955 --> 22:29.739
I just--I panicked, you know?

22:29.783 --> 22:32.699
I just tried scaring him
with my knife.

22:32.742 --> 22:37.443
I did not think he was gonna
fight back.

22:37.486 --> 22:39.923
- What were they having you
look for?

22:39.967 --> 22:41.621
Is that--is that what
they're looking for now?

22:41.664 --> 22:44.363
- It's like some sort of--
some sort of book.

22:44.406 --> 22:47.017
It's got a brown moleskin cover
and green binding.

22:47.061 --> 22:49.150
- Why would the Exiles want
something like that?

22:49.193 --> 22:51.282
- I don't know, man.
They didn't tell me.

22:51.326 --> 22:52.849
I know they want it.

22:52.893 --> 22:55.548
And I couldn't find it anywhere
so now they're looking.

22:57.114 --> 23:00.640
Lucas, if they don't find
this thing,

23:00.683 --> 23:02.816
I don't know what
they're gonna do next.

23:02.859 --> 23:05.775
[tense music]

23:05.819 --> 23:10.780
♪

23:10.824 --> 23:13.217
- We're just gonna have to
help them.

23:13.261 --> 23:16.873
♪

23:16.917 --> 23:19.920
- I still don't see him.

23:21.051 --> 23:24.881
- Lucas is going to be fine.

23:24.925 --> 23:26.448
- What if the last thing
I said was that

23:26.492 --> 23:28.058
I didn't want to move in
with him?

23:28.102 --> 23:29.843
- Did you tell him why
you said no?

23:29.886 --> 23:32.411
- About Aaron?
- Yeah.

23:32.454 --> 23:34.587
- No.

23:34.630 --> 23:38.373
Even with Lucas,
who I really like,

23:38.417 --> 23:39.766
whenever I try to be open,

23:39.809 --> 23:41.245
all of a sudden,
Aaron's in my head

23:41.289 --> 23:42.986
and there's no getting rid
of him.

23:43.030 --> 23:44.292
It's like with those
red flowers

23:44.335 --> 23:47.077
that he used to draw
that we saw down here.

23:47.121 --> 23:48.992
Everywhere I turn,
he seems to be there

23:49.036 --> 23:51.255
and I don't know what to do.

23:53.910 --> 23:55.477
- Get out here. Come on!

23:55.521 --> 23:56.609
- No!
- Let go of her!

23:56.652 --> 23:58.741
- Hey! Let them go.

23:58.785 --> 24:03.659
♪

24:03.703 --> 24:05.400
I have what you want.

24:05.444 --> 24:07.446
Brown moleskin book with
a green binding, right?

24:07.489 --> 24:10.231
♪

24:10.274 --> 24:13.060
- Did he just say--
- Yeah.

24:14.670 --> 24:16.455
- How do you know that?

24:16.498 --> 24:18.282
- All you need to know is
I can take you to it.

24:18.326 --> 24:22.548
- If you know about the book,
what's inside it?

24:22.591 --> 24:24.550
You're lying.

24:24.593 --> 24:26.334
- No, he's telling the truth.

24:27.814 --> 24:29.859
But he only knows half of it.

24:29.903 --> 24:30.904
The book you're talking about
has got

24:30.947 --> 24:34.734
numbers and symbols in it.

24:34.777 --> 24:37.171
- How do you know this?

24:37.214 --> 24:39.216
- Because it belonged to
somebody I know.

24:41.828 --> 24:44.134
His name was Aaron.

24:44.178 --> 24:47.616
And I don't know why
he'd have something you want,

24:47.660 --> 24:49.966
but I know he never let it go

24:50.010 --> 24:52.926
'cause I buried him with it.

25:00.890 --> 25:02.544
- Where is he buried?

25:02.588 --> 25:04.415
- We can show you.

25:07.114 --> 25:09.246
- You will go with
five of my men to the grave.

25:09.290 --> 25:11.161
You will dig up the book
and bring it here.

25:11.205 --> 25:13.250
But if you are not back
by sundown...

25:13.294 --> 25:15.514
- [grunts]

25:15.557 --> 25:17.341
- He dies.

25:22.999 --> 25:23.391
.

25:23.434 --> 25:26.263
[tense music]

25:26.307 --> 25:28.004
- You sure
you're doing that right?

25:28.048 --> 25:30.354
- Dad helped me learn Morse
code for a Girl Scout badge.

25:30.398 --> 25:32.356
- That doesn't inspire
a lot of confidence.

25:32.400 --> 25:34.576
- Mirror flashes can be seen
a hundred miles away.

25:34.620 --> 25:35.751
I'm flashing it
towards the building.

25:35.795 --> 25:38.667
And if Dad looks back,
he will see it.

25:42.758 --> 25:45.848
- Hey. Check it out.

25:45.892 --> 25:48.111
♪

25:48.155 --> 25:49.635
- Come on, let's go.

25:49.678 --> 25:52.551
- Keep moving.

25:52.594 --> 25:54.248
- I have to change the message.

25:54.291 --> 25:56.685
- Why?

25:56.729 --> 25:58.731
- Because if Dad has
any chance of saving us,

25:58.774 --> 26:01.168
he has to target
the small group first.

26:01.211 --> 26:04.214
It's basic tactics.

26:04.258 --> 26:06.477
- Girl Scouts are badass.

26:06.521 --> 26:07.696
- [chuckles softly]

26:07.740 --> 26:11.657
♪

26:11.700 --> 26:14.616
- Whoa, hang on.

26:18.577 --> 26:20.579
- It's like I taught Izzy.

26:20.622 --> 26:22.058
It's her.

26:22.102 --> 26:23.103
- What's she saying?

26:23.146 --> 26:24.800
- Um...

26:28.108 --> 26:31.807
A-T-T...

26:32.634 --> 26:36.333
S-T.

26:36.377 --> 26:39.467
Attack, Exiles, East.

26:39.510 --> 26:41.077
- I think she's saying
there's a group moving east.

26:41.121 --> 26:42.209
We should take them out,

26:42.252 --> 26:43.819
then we can hit the clearing.
- Smart.

26:43.863 --> 26:45.952
- No. No, no, no. We know what
the Exiles are capable of.

26:45.995 --> 26:48.084
They have my family.
That's where we go first.

26:48.128 --> 26:50.260
- Your kid's got eyes on a
situation that says different.

26:50.304 --> 26:51.958
- Sam! My wife is injured
on that bus.

26:52.001 --> 26:55.744
- Gavin, we know that you want
to protect your family,

26:55.788 --> 27:00.140
but Izzy's sharp.
Think it through.

27:00.183 --> 27:03.230
So what are we gonna do?

27:04.753 --> 27:06.320
- Dr. Coleman.

27:06.363 --> 27:07.669
- I asked to see you
before I leave.

27:07.713 --> 27:09.410
- Of course.

27:09.453 --> 27:11.151
How are you?

27:11.194 --> 27:13.806
- Well...

27:13.849 --> 27:15.329
nothing in this world
is guaranteed.

27:15.372 --> 27:16.939
But according to your doctors,

27:16.983 --> 27:19.681
my recovery is moving in
the right direction.

27:19.725 --> 27:22.641
Just need to come back in a few
days for the next treatment.

27:22.684 --> 27:25.078
Still, I wouldn't be
doing my job

27:25.121 --> 27:27.428
if I left without following up
on your dream.

27:27.471 --> 27:29.038
- I appreciate your tenacity,

27:29.082 --> 27:31.345
but I haven't been able to
remember anything else.

27:31.388 --> 27:34.130
- You know, sometimes
psychiatrists need to do

27:34.174 --> 27:35.697
outside research

27:35.741 --> 27:39.309
in order to better understand
the symbolism

27:39.353 --> 27:41.398
within the dreams of
our patients.

27:41.442 --> 27:42.878
So I took it upon myself to

27:42.922 --> 27:45.968
ask around the building about
those evergreens,

27:46.012 --> 27:49.842
see what they might signify
to a man like you.

27:49.885 --> 27:51.147
But the thing is,

27:51.191 --> 27:53.497
there hasn't been a shipment
of them all year,

27:53.541 --> 27:56.718
which suggests you weren't
being entirely truthful.

27:56.762 --> 27:58.894
In order for me to help you,
James,

27:58.938 --> 28:01.114
you have to tell me
what's really going on.

28:01.157 --> 28:03.290
- [chuckles wryly]

28:05.292 --> 28:07.120
It wasn't a dream that woke me.

28:07.163 --> 28:09.557
It was a nightmare...

28:11.428 --> 28:14.867
About the day Isiah was taken.

28:14.910 --> 28:16.172
- Tell me about it.

28:16.216 --> 28:19.828
It could be the key to
solving your insomnia.

28:19.872 --> 28:21.612
- I dreamed I went to go
and wake him up

28:21.656 --> 28:23.745
and I found his bed empty.

28:23.789 --> 28:27.401
And the moment I saw it,
I knew he was gone.

28:27.444 --> 28:28.924
And I still searched.

28:28.968 --> 28:31.753
I looked everywhere, even
though I knew it was hopeless.

28:31.797 --> 28:35.757
And the dream, it was so real.

28:35.801 --> 28:37.890
It felt like I'd lost him
all over again.

28:37.933 --> 28:40.936
And it even--
it brought back, um--

28:40.980 --> 28:42.459
- What did it bring back?

28:42.503 --> 28:45.027
- When I lost him,
the emptiness,

28:45.071 --> 28:48.074
it made me...

28:48.117 --> 28:50.598
do something unthinkable.

28:50.641 --> 28:53.557
[soft somber music]

28:53.601 --> 28:57.126
♪

28:57.170 --> 29:00.173
- You tried to harm yourself.

29:00.216 --> 29:02.392
- I went to my gun case.

29:02.436 --> 29:05.656
I unlocked a pistol...

29:05.700 --> 29:08.181
put it to the side of my head,

29:08.224 --> 29:10.661
and I pulled the trigger.

29:10.705 --> 29:13.142
And it should have killed me,

29:13.186 --> 29:17.886
but the gun's chamber was empty

29:17.930 --> 29:19.496
because I'd taken out
all the bullets

29:19.540 --> 29:22.804
to keep Isiah safe.

29:22.848 --> 29:26.503
So even though Isiah was gone,

29:26.547 --> 29:28.810
he still saved me.

29:28.854 --> 29:31.508
And then the dream just
made it all come back.

29:31.552 --> 29:36.383
- It's a terrible feeling.

29:36.426 --> 29:38.124
In the light of day,

29:38.167 --> 29:42.215
you must be able to see that
you have your son back.

29:42.258 --> 29:44.130
- But I don't.

29:44.173 --> 29:50.092
My son will never trust me.

29:50.136 --> 29:53.922
And I don't know where to go
with that.

29:53.966 --> 29:56.359
- What you're feeling is
normal

29:56.403 --> 29:59.536
and we can work on it.

29:59.580 --> 30:02.017
You can have
a relationship with Gavin

30:02.061 --> 30:05.325
and still hold space for
the memory of Isiah.

30:05.368 --> 30:09.764
♪

30:09.808 --> 30:14.464
- I love imagining him here.

30:14.508 --> 30:16.205
The Bio Bay was
his favorite place.

30:16.249 --> 30:19.295
He, um--

30:19.339 --> 30:21.036
he would color here every day.

30:21.080 --> 30:23.604
Here--you know, here are
a few of his drawings.

30:23.647 --> 30:25.606
[tablet chimes]
There.

30:25.649 --> 30:32.787
♪

30:32.831 --> 30:35.572
- Wait. Would you--
would you mind going back one?

30:35.616 --> 30:38.271
- Huh?
- Yeah.

30:38.314 --> 30:40.229
A blue moon.

30:40.273 --> 30:43.929
- It's beautiful, isn't it?

30:43.972 --> 30:47.236
- Yeah. It is.

30:47.280 --> 30:50.109
[ominous music]

30:50.152 --> 30:54.243
- [grunts]

30:54.287 --> 30:56.289
- You OK?

30:56.332 --> 30:58.900
- I just want this to be over.

31:02.121 --> 31:04.819
[gasping]

31:07.953 --> 31:10.738
- Hey, I can get the book.

31:10.781 --> 31:13.480
- No, no.
No, I need to do this.

31:21.705 --> 31:25.013
This book was so important
to him.

31:25.057 --> 31:28.625
He never let us near it.

31:28.669 --> 31:30.889
I'm not gonna be afraid
anymore.

31:33.152 --> 31:36.111
[tense music]

31:36.155 --> 31:43.075
♪

31:50.082 --> 31:51.126
- Hand it over.

31:51.170 --> 31:52.345
Now.

31:52.388 --> 31:59.526
♪

32:06.098 --> 32:10.319
[gunshots]

32:10.363 --> 32:12.234
- Live or die, it's up to you.

32:12.278 --> 32:15.150
♪

32:15.194 --> 32:16.586
- We have to get to
the clearing.

32:16.630 --> 32:18.545
Grab their weapons,
tie them up. Let's move.

32:21.591 --> 32:21.809
.

32:21.852 --> 32:23.854
[dramatic music]

32:23.898 --> 32:25.900
- Time's almost up.

32:25.944 --> 32:27.684
- [chuckles softly]

32:27.728 --> 32:29.382
You know what?

32:29.425 --> 32:31.688
Before I die,
I just have one thing to say.

32:31.732 --> 32:34.430
As a cultural anthropologist,

32:34.474 --> 32:36.780
I've had a unique opportunity
to study your group

32:36.824 --> 32:39.609
from a number of different
ethnographic perspectives:

32:39.653 --> 32:43.265
cognitive, political,
developmental, psychological,

32:43.309 --> 32:44.701
even transpersonal.

32:44.745 --> 32:47.313
And I have to say that
on every level,

32:47.356 --> 32:50.446
you are all an epic fail.

32:50.490 --> 32:52.579
♪

32:52.622 --> 32:54.059
- [grunting]

32:54.102 --> 32:55.930
- Ah!

32:55.974 --> 32:57.410
- In the trees!
- Look out!

32:57.453 --> 32:59.107
- Come on!
[indistinct shouting]

32:59.151 --> 33:00.369
- Get him!

33:00.413 --> 33:03.503
[grunting]

33:08.638 --> 33:11.293
[gun cocks]

33:11.337 --> 33:14.427
- On your knees! Now!

33:14.470 --> 33:16.037
- [snarls]

33:16.081 --> 33:17.821
- Taamet!

33:17.865 --> 33:24.785
♪

33:26.917 --> 33:29.616
[breathing heavily]

33:33.185 --> 33:35.752
- You see him?
- No.

33:35.796 --> 33:37.319
- Damn it.

33:41.062 --> 33:42.063
- [grunts]

33:42.107 --> 33:44.935
[both straining]

33:44.979 --> 33:46.850
- Ah!
[blade rings]

33:46.894 --> 33:48.678
- [grunts]
- No--

33:49.853 --> 33:51.290
- [shouts]

33:54.467 --> 33:57.905
- [grunts]

33:57.948 --> 34:00.081
- [panting]

34:00.125 --> 34:03.084
- [panting]
- [sucking breath]

34:03.128 --> 34:05.869
[groans]

34:05.913 --> 34:08.871
- [panting]

34:08.916 --> 34:11.918
- [groaning]

34:11.962 --> 34:14.922
[tense music]

34:14.965 --> 34:16.837
♪

34:16.880 --> 34:20.362
- I saw that James has
scheduled more time with you.

34:20.406 --> 34:21.623
Things must have gone well.

34:21.668 --> 34:23.670
- I think so.

34:23.713 --> 34:24.888
- We're out of the building,
Doctor.

34:24.931 --> 34:27.500
We can talk openly.

34:27.543 --> 34:30.284
- Kiera...

34:30.329 --> 34:31.938
what is Project Blue Moon?

34:31.982 --> 34:33.331
- I don't know.

34:33.375 --> 34:36.117
Project Blue Moon is
the first Lazarus operation

34:36.161 --> 34:39.120
James has locked me out of.

34:39.164 --> 34:43.472
- Blue Moon is a drawing
made by his son Isiah.

34:43.516 --> 34:46.693
Does that mean anything to you?

34:46.735 --> 34:48.347
- James has been talking about
what he wants to do

34:48.389 --> 34:49.956
once the machine is fixed.

34:50.000 --> 34:53.612
And now, I think he wants to
use it to start over.

34:56.442 --> 34:59.619
- Losing Isiah is
James' biggest regret.

34:59.662 --> 35:01.142
If he could have
anything he wanted,

35:01.186 --> 35:02.404
I think he would go back
in time

35:02.448 --> 35:04.406
and make sure that
never happened.

35:04.450 --> 35:06.713
- He can't do this.
- I agree.

35:06.756 --> 35:10.108
If he does, Isiah will never
leave his side.

35:10.151 --> 35:11.979
He won't go to 1988,

35:12.022 --> 35:13.807
won't meet Eve, have kids.

35:13.850 --> 35:15.765
- This is about more than
just Gavin.

35:15.809 --> 35:17.158
This is about you.

35:17.202 --> 35:18.855
Once James starts over
with Isiah,

35:18.899 --> 35:20.988
everything from that point
will change.

35:21.031 --> 35:22.424
There'll be no
La Brea sinkhole.

35:22.468 --> 35:24.165
You will never come to
this building

35:24.209 --> 35:27.255
for cancer treatment, Ty.

35:27.299 --> 35:29.823
You'll die.

35:29.866 --> 35:34.741
♪

35:34.784 --> 35:36.873
- [grunting]

35:36.917 --> 35:37.831
- You guys all right?

35:37.874 --> 35:39.572
- Yeah.

35:45.795 --> 35:49.364
- [groaning weakly]

35:49.408 --> 35:53.151
- Gavin, they were--
they were looking for this.

35:53.194 --> 35:55.718
Why would the Exiles want this?

35:55.762 --> 35:57.764
- Can I see?

36:00.767 --> 36:02.464
Hang on.

36:04.118 --> 36:05.815
Hold this.

36:05.859 --> 36:07.339
Look.

36:07.382 --> 36:09.602
James gave me this page of
Moore's research.

36:09.645 --> 36:11.908
It fits.
- I don't understand, man.

36:11.952 --> 36:15.347
- This must be Moore's journal,
his complete work.

36:15.390 --> 36:16.783
It's our way home.

36:20.700 --> 36:22.528
Hey.

36:22.571 --> 36:26.227
Hey, Taamet.
- [grunting]

36:26.271 --> 36:29.012
- Hey!

36:29.056 --> 36:31.189
James sent me to find this.

36:31.232 --> 36:32.320
- [groans]

36:32.364 --> 36:34.322
- Did he send you to
get it, too?

36:34.366 --> 36:35.454
- Not James.

36:35.497 --> 36:39.197
- Not James.
Then who?

36:39.240 --> 36:40.546
- Kiera.

36:40.589 --> 36:44.854
[groans]

36:44.898 --> 36:51.818
♪

37:06.311 --> 37:08.878
- Come on. Let's get going.

37:08.922 --> 37:10.402
- [sighs]

37:16.408 --> 37:18.453
How you holding up?

37:21.326 --> 37:24.067
- The man who took me had

37:24.111 --> 37:28.071
a book from 10,000 B.C.

37:28.115 --> 37:33.381
that might be the key to
getting us home, so...

37:33.425 --> 37:35.818
- [clears throat]

37:35.862 --> 37:37.907
It's a lot.

37:37.951 --> 37:43.913
- Aaron...took us to La Brea
that day.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.611
He parked the car and told us
to stay put.

37:45.654 --> 37:50.572
It's like he knew
the sinkhole was coming,

37:50.616 --> 37:54.184
like he wanted to be there.

37:54.228 --> 37:57.013
It's just...

37:57.057 --> 37:59.712
none of it--
none of it makes any sense.

38:03.019 --> 38:05.195
[chuckles softly]

38:05.239 --> 38:09.635
Guess if you thought
I was damaged goods before...

38:09.678 --> 38:12.725
- What are you talking about?

38:12.768 --> 38:15.249
Hey.

38:15.293 --> 38:19.819
I--I think you're
the strongest person

38:19.862 --> 38:24.389
I've ever met.

38:24.432 --> 38:27.740
I wouldn't want you
any other way.

38:31.613 --> 38:34.790
[soft music]

38:34.834 --> 38:41.754
♪

38:48.195 --> 38:50.328
- What are you doing?

38:50.371 --> 38:54.897
- We are going to your car.

38:54.941 --> 38:56.464
I'm moving in.

38:56.508 --> 39:03.645
♪

39:16.397 --> 39:19.400
- [inhales slowly]

39:19.444 --> 39:22.751
[exhales]

39:22.795 --> 39:24.274
- Hey, hey.
- [gasps]

39:24.318 --> 39:25.667
- Hey, no, no, no, no, no.

39:25.711 --> 39:27.365
Josh and Izzy are outside.
They're safe.

39:27.408 --> 39:28.366
- OK.
- It's OK.

39:28.409 --> 39:30.455
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

39:30.498 --> 39:32.370
- [softly] Thank you.

39:32.413 --> 39:35.329
- I'm sorry.

39:35.373 --> 39:36.852
I know you didn't want me
to go today.

39:36.896 --> 39:39.986
- No, it's all right. It's OK.
- It's not.

39:40.029 --> 39:42.380
[softly] It's not.

39:43.598 --> 39:48.473
But I did find something.

39:54.392 --> 39:56.437
It's what we were looking for;

39:56.481 --> 39:59.005
all of Dr. Moore's research.

39:59.048 --> 40:01.268
With this,
we can fix the machine.

40:01.311 --> 40:02.312
- This is amazing.

40:02.356 --> 40:03.879
- Yeah.
[chuckles]

40:03.923 --> 40:08.536
It's also what
the Exiles were looking for.

40:08.580 --> 40:11.234
And Kiera sent them.

40:11.278 --> 40:14.368
- Kiera?
- Mm-hmm.

40:14.412 --> 40:20.679
I don't know if she was working
for James or against him,

40:20.722 --> 40:22.507
or for some other reason
entirely,

40:22.550 --> 40:27.076
but it was her.

40:27.120 --> 40:28.904
Hey, look, I know we haven't
been on the same page

40:28.948 --> 40:31.211
about this.

40:31.254 --> 40:34.562
I want us to be.

40:34.606 --> 40:36.390
I want us to figure this out
together.

40:36.434 --> 40:38.436
- I do too.

40:40.612 --> 40:43.136
- There's something else.

40:43.179 --> 40:44.833
- What?

40:44.877 --> 40:46.618
- Someone's here to see you.

40:52.014 --> 40:54.974
[soft music]

40:55.017 --> 40:57.280
♪

40:57.324 --> 40:59.413
- Levi.

40:59.457 --> 41:02.982
♪

41:03.025 --> 41:05.854
I can't believe it.
You're back.

41:08.161 --> 41:09.989
Hey.

41:12.252 --> 41:15.516
Wow. The gray suits you.

41:15.560 --> 41:17.605
- Older and wiser.
- Mm.

41:17.649 --> 41:19.477
- At least that's what
they say.

41:19.520 --> 41:22.567
- What are you doing here?

41:25.657 --> 41:29.487
- What I told Gavin
wasn't the truth.

41:29.530 --> 41:31.140
- What do you mean?

41:31.184 --> 41:33.229
- I told him that I had a plan
to bring everyone home,

41:33.273 --> 41:34.579
but the truth is, I don't.

41:34.622 --> 41:35.841
The reason I'm here is to do

41:35.884 --> 41:38.931
the one thing that can set
everything right.

41:38.974 --> 41:41.063
And I need your help to do it.

41:41.107 --> 41:42.587
[music darkens]

41:42.630 --> 41:44.327
I'm here to kill James.

41:44.371 --> 41:46.199
♪

41:49.332 --> 41:49.681
.

41:49.724 --> 41:52.510
[dramatic music]

41:52.553 --> 41:59.647
♪
